The article highlights the contributions of veterans in the United States who own nearly 2.5 million small businesses. It emphasizes their role in pursuing the American Dream and acknowledges their impact on the country's economy. Veteran-owned small businesses employ over 5 million people and generate more than $1 trillion in sales annually. The article mentions efforts by the administration to support veterans in their professional goals, including providing federal student loan forgiveness for disabled veterans. It also mentions the lowest recorded veteran unemployment rate and initiatives like Boots to Business, which help veterans apply their military skills to entrepreneurship. The article concludes by recognizing the significant contributions of veterans to the prosperity and success of the nation.